(133, 1, '2020-05-15 22:58:50', '2020-05-15 22:58:50', '<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":66.66} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":129,\"width\":499,\"height\":857,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/finalproject/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/image-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-129\" width=\"499\" height=\"857\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":33.33} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Common invasive ventilators are in short supply. While numerous companies have stepped forward to scale up production of the expensive products (usually between $25,000 and $50,000), the need for equipment continues to grow.<br>“If a patient goes to a hospital, and all of the ventilators are taken up, the only other option the patient has is to have a nurse or, God forbid, a loved one, actually ventilate that patient by hand,” University of Minnesota Earl Bakken Medical Center lab supervisor Aaron Tucker told the DeviceTalks Weekly Podcast.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Those who are infected with COVID-19 may have little to no symptoms. You may not know you have symptoms of COVID-19 because they are similar to a cold or flu.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Symptoms have included:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>cough</li><li>fever</li><li>difficulty breathing</li><li>pneumonia in both lungs</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In severe cases, infection can lead to death.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Symptoms may take up to 14 days to appear after exposure to COVID-19. This is the longest known incubation period for this disease.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Recent evidence indicates that the virus can be transmitted to others from someone who is infected but not showing symptoms. This includes people who:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>have not yet developed symptoms (pre-symptomatic)</li><li>never develop symptoms (asymptomatic)</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While experts know that these kinds of transmissions are happening among those in close contact or in close physical settings, it is not known to what extent. This means it is extremely important to follow the proven&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/diseases/2019-novel-coronavirus-infection/prevention-risks.html#p\">preventative measures</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->', 'COVID-19', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '114-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-05-15 22:58:50', '2020-05-15 22:58:50', '', 114, 'http://localhost/finalproject/2020/05/15/114-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(134, 1, '2020-05-15 22:59:48', '2020-05-15 22:59:48', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 id=\"p\"></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Think you might have COVID-19?</strong><br><a href=\"https://ca.thrive.health/covid19/en\">Take a self-assessment</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Canadians should continue to think ahead about the actions that they can take to stay healthy and prevent the spread of COVID-19 in Canada. This includes staying at home as much as possible and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/diseases/2019-novel-coronavirus-infection/being-prepared.html#a2\">being prepared</a>&nbsp;in case you or a family member becomes ill. Everyone should be practising physical (social) distancing. Even if you do not have symptoms of COVID-19, you could become infected by others.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As we continue to see transmission of the virus within different communities, we know that everyone must take precautions, even those who have not travelled outside of Canada.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In an effort to prevent the spread of COVID-19 within communities and across the country, all Canadians are advised to:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>stay at home unless you have to go to work<ul><li>talk to your employer about working at home if possible</li></ul></li><li>avoid all non-essential trips in your community</li><li>do not gather in groups</li><li>limit contact with people at higher risk, such as older adults and those in poor health</li><li>go outside to exercise but stay close to home</li><li>if you leave your home, always keep a distance of at least 2 arms lengths (approximately 2 metres) from others<ul><li>household contacts (people you live with) do not need to distance from each other unless they are sick or have travelled in the last 14 days</li></ul></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":137,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/finalproject/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/ADHA_covid_webpage_header_top.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-137\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>You can go for a walk if you:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>have not been diagnosed with COVID-19</li><li>do not have symptoms of COVID-19</li><li>have not travelled outside of Canada in the past 14 days</li><li>are not in quarantine (self-isolating)</li><li>are not isolating</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you go out for a walk, do not congregate and always practise physical (social) distancing by keeping at least 2 metres apart from others at all times.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"social\">Physical (social) distancing</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Together, we can slow the spread of COVID-19 by making a conscious effort to keep a physical distance between each other.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/social-distancing.html\">Physical (social) distancing</a>&nbsp;is proven to be one of the most effective ways to reduce the spread of illness during an outbreak.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This means making changes in your everyday routines to minimize close contact with others, including:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>avoiding crowded places and non-essential gatherings</li><li>avoiding common greetings, such as handshakes</li><li>limiting contact with people at higher risk like older adults and those in poor health</li><li>keeping a distance of at least 2 arms-length (approximately 2 metres) from others</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":138,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/finalproject/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/ASTMH_AJTMH-Coronaviurs-banner-Copy-1024x313.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-138\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"hygiene\">Hygiene</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Proper hygiene can help reduce the risk of infection or spreading infection to others:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds, especially after using the washroom and when preparing food<ul><li>use alcohol-based&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/health-canada/services/drugs-health-products/disinfectants/covid-19/hand-sanitizer.html\">hand sanitizer</a>&nbsp;if soap and water are not available</li></ul></li><li>when coughing or sneezing:<ul><li>cough or sneeze into a tissue or the bend of your arm, not your hand</li><li>dispose of any tissues you have used as soon as possible in a lined waste basket and wash your hands afterwards</li></ul></li><li>avoid touching your eyes, nose, or mouth with unwashed hands</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":139,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/finalproject/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/shutterstock_1680120298-1-700x392-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-139\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Cleaning</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coronaviruses&nbsp;are one of the easiest types of viruses to kill with the appropriate disinfectant product when used according to the label directions. Health Canada has published a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/health-canada/services/drugs-health-products/disinfectants/covid-19/list.html\">list of hard surface disinfectants</a>&nbsp;that are likely to be effective for use against COVID-19.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although they do not claim to kill COVID-19, cleaners can play a role in limiting the transfer of microorganisms. Health Canada recommends cleaning high-touch hard surfaces often, using either regular household cleaners or diluted bleach according to the label directions. This bleach solution should be prepared according to the instructions on the label or in a ratio of 250 mL (1 cup) of water per 5 mL (1 teaspoon) of bleach. Directions are based on bleach that is 5% sodium hypochlorite, to give a 0.1% sodium hypochlorite solution. Never mix bleach with other chemical products and use it in a well-ventilated area.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/health-canada/services/home-safety/household-chemical-safety.html\">Special precautions</a>&nbsp;must be used when cleaning with bleach to avoid serious incidents.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>These surfaces include:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>toilets</li><li>phones</li><li>electronics</li><li>door handles</li><li>bedside tables</li><li>television remotes</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Refer to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/cleaning-disinfecting-public-spaces.html\">guidance on cleaning and disinfecting public spaces</a>&nbsp;for more information.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"wm\">Wearing masks or face coverings</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Medical masks, including surgical, medical procedure face masks and respirators (like N95 masks), must be kept for health care workers and others providing direct care to COVID-19 patients.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Wearing a non-medical mask or face covering while out in public is optional. If you do choose to wear one, refer to our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/diseases/2019-novel-coronavirus-infection/prevention-risks/about-non-medical-masks-face-coverings.html\">guidelines on wearing non-medical masks and how to make your own</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Masks alone will not prevent the spread of COVID-19. You must consistently and strictly adhere to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/diseases/2019-novel-coronavirus-infection/prevention-risks.html#hygiene\">good hygiene</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/diseases/2019-novel-coronavirus-infection/prevention-risks.html#p\">public health measures</a>, including frequent&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/reduce-spread-covid-19-wash-your-hands.html\">hand washing</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/social-distancing.html\">physical (social) distancing</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Preventing coronavirus', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'preventing-coronavirus', '', '', '2020-05-15 23:12:03', '2020-05-15 23:12:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost/finalproject/?page_id=134', 0, 'page', '', 0),
